    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-03-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1897</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Tobacco embargo. Indemnification for further detention less important than
                    immediate release. Factories Chicago, New York, and elsewhere idle in
                    consequence of embargo. Urge prompt compliance with Spanish promise to release
                    tobaccos bought or contracted for prior to decree of embargo. Spanish minister
                    here has promised to urge early action on his Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sherman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
